name: Kaley Cuoco (JG)
description:
Kaley Cuoco is an American actress, mainly known for her role as Penny in The Big Bang Theory series.

450-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my new settings. This is a bit of an experiment, mainly based on this (ongoing) conversation, particularly on the comments and expertise shared by @7016jayAlex, for which I want to give him special thanks. Basically, what's changed is that I have reduced my dataset to 18 images and increased my gradient accumulation steps to 6, so that I now run a full epoch per step (3 batch size * 6 gradient = 18, the exact number of pics in my dataset). That way, I can achieve similar results to the ones I've been posting until now with around 400, 450 steps, as in this case. I gotta say it takes me basically the same time to train, though. I'll train a few more TIs following this new procedure and then decide whether I like it better or worse (or maybe exactly the same) as my previous one. For now, I gotta say it looks pretty good! :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)
